Practical No: 9

Objective: To understand and practice the process of taking a backup of a MySQL database 
to ensure data security and disaster recovery using Ubuntu.

Step 4: Login to MySQL sudo 
mysql -u root -p

Step 5: Create Sample Database 
CREATE DATABASE college_db; 

USE college_db; 

CREATE TABLE students (id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT, name VARCHAR(50), course 
VARCHAR(50)); 

INSERT INTO students(name, course) VALUES 
('Rahul','BCA'),('Sneha','Bsc'),('Amit','Btech');

Step 6: Take Backup mysqldump -u root -p college_db 
> college_backup.sql ( new terminal )

Step 7: Delete Database for Testing 
DROP DATABASE college_db;

Step 8: Recreate Database 
CREATE DATABASE college_db;

Step 9: Restore Backup 
mysql -u root -p college_db < college_backup.sql 

Step 10: Verify Data 
USE college_db; SELECT * 
FROM students;
















































































